
DOM basics: Browser me HTML elements ko JS se select/update karna (button click pe UI change).

Event loop: JS ka system jo decide karta hai async code (promises, setTimeout) kis order me chalega.

Closures: Function apne outer scope ke variables ko “yaad” rakhta hai.

Hoisting / scope: Variables/functions memory me kab aur kis area me available hote hain.

this / bind / call / apply: this ka reference control karna aur function ko different object context me run karna.

Prototypes / classes: JS me objects inheritance ka base system (classes iski cleaner syntax).

Debounce / throttle: Frequent events (scroll/search) ko control karke performance improve karna.

LocalStorage / sessionStorage: Browser me data store karna (token, theme, cart).

Error handling patterns: Errors ko properly catch/log/handle karna without app crash.

TypeScript: JS + types, jisse bugs kam hote hain aur production code safe hota hai.